******
[3] Montana
Date: Fri 30 Aug 2013
Source: KPAX, Montana Television Network (MTN) report [edited]
http://www.kpax.com/news/pertussis-reports-pour-in-from-around-mt/


Towns and cities across Montana are still reporting cases of the whooping cough [pertussis]. During a health board meeting earlier in August 2013, it was revealed that 225 cases of pertussis were reported between June 2012 and May 2013. That's an average of nearly 19 cases a month -- and 25 more cases were reported in June 2013.

Data for the month of August [2013] was not made available in that report, but the Flathead City-County Health Department tells us they are still confirming cases of pertussis in the Flathead.

The Butte-Silver Bow Health Department is also dealing with an outbreak of whooping cough. Health officials say so far in 2013 there have been 27 cases of pertussis. In 2012, there were only 2.

Meanwhile, Anaconda Deer Lodge County is also seeing a huge increase with 36 diagnosed cases already in 2013. In 2012, there was just one.

--
